2 awesome things about Los Angeles:
yummy.com- you can order anything and they deliver it to your door anytime.

The radio stations- they play queen on the classic rock channel waaay more than in Naples, and not just Bohemian Rhapsody. There's even and indie station haha.

Dukers has a hole in his ear. I need to find him an earring.

I've been in L.A. for about 2 months now.

It's not all it's cracked up to be. 
It's a very pretty city with hills and mountains and homeless people everywhere.

The weather is amazing, It's never hot and always sunny. NO HUMIDITY!

I still haven't found a job, our apartment is great but rent is ridiculous and I have no money.

I never thought I'd say this but I miss naples terribly.
Maybe I just miss the security of naples, knowing where everything is or not having to drive on 5 different highways, or knowing that I'll always have a job there.

Maybe if I had a decent job and wasn't so stressed about money I wouldn't want to go home so bad.

It gets better right?
